text: Toluca Cathedral is a large Modern Catholic cathedral in Mexico and is found in the city of Toluca in Mexico (state). The first cathedral was much larger but was demolished so that The Headrow could be made wider. The new cathedral is next to where the old cathedral was. ==Bishops== * Francisco Javier Chavolla Ramos == Other websites == Category:Roman Catholic cathedrals in Mexico Category:Buildings and structures in Mexico (state) Category:Toluca Category:Cultural heritage monuments in Mexico (state)
